The paper deals with the problem of learning a discrete distribution in the presence of malicious data sources, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithms presented in the paper involve computational techniques such as tensor approximation and optimization, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the possibility of adversarial attacks on the data, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
